#327 doesn't address it. It only allows you to go from a spark dataframe directly to a local pandas variable.

You cannot read locally from a csv in your computer and send it to the remote spark cluster. If you want to read a csv file, the file must be in the cluster storage. In the case of HDInsight, that will be either the container for the cluster in your Azure Storage account or in ADLS.

